How hard can it be?

168
00:14:13,400 --> 00:14:15,200
Not too hard, Daniel-<i>san</i>...

169
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:20,500
...if Miyagi have money for lease,
deposit, fix-up.

170
00:14:21,500 --> 00:14:24,700
But since we build house
for Yukie in Okinawa...

171
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:27,900
...money very short supply.

172
00:14:28,000 --> 00:14:29,200
"Supply"?

173
00:14:30,500 --> 00:14:32,100
Supplies are us.

174
00:14:34,500 --> 00:14:37,600
Thank you, Daniel-<i>san</i>,
but that not money.

175
00:14:38,100 --> 00:14:42,600
It looks like money. Smells like money.
Good money. Smell that.

176
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:44,700
Smell like college education.

177
00:14:44,800 --> 00:14:47,000
I know, Mr. Miyagi,
but I have a great idea...

178
00:14:47,200 --> 00:14:48,600
Daniel-<i>san</i>.

179
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:50,400
No idea.

180
00:14:51,900 --> 00:14:53,700
Discussion closed.

181
00:14:54,400 --> 00:14:56,200
But what about your dream?

182
00:14:56,200 --> 00:14:59,700
And, Mr. Miyagi, no offence,
but if you miss the train this time...

183
00:14:59,700 --> 00:15:02,500
...there may not be another one
for a long time.

184
00:15:02,600 --> 00:15:04,500
Then Miyagi take bus.

185
00:15:29,000 --> 00:15:32,300
Revenge? Of course you want revenge.
I'm gonna get it for you.

186
00:15:32,400 --> 00:15:36,300
The day you step off the plane, you're
the biggest <i>dojo</i> operator in the valley.

187
00:15:36,400 --> 00:15:38,200
<i>What are you talking about?</i>

188
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:41,500
I bought 20 locations today.
Yours, 100 percent.

189
00:15:41,500 --> 00:15:44,600
You are back, my man,
bigger and badder than ever.

190
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:46,500
<i>You're a sweetheart, that's great!</i>

191
00:15:46,800 --> 00:15:48,800
But what about those two jerks?

192
00:15:48,900 --> 00:15:52,400
<i>Those two jerks are taking up</i>
<i>100 percent of my time from now on.</i>

193
00:15:52,500 --> 00:15:55,400
So just have patience.
I'm just getting things rolling.

194
00:15:55,500 --> 00:15:59,500
When I'm finished with that kid,
he'll be begging me to be his teacher.

195
00:15:59,600 --> 00:16:01,600
You know what he's gonna learn from me?

196
00:16:01,700 --> 00:16:06,600
Pain in every part of his body
and fear in every part of his mind.

197
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:09,900
And here's the kicker:
he's gonna thank me for it.

198
00:16:10,400 --> 00:16:11,500
What about the old man?

199
00:16:11,800 --> 00:16:13,300
Him I hurt for the kid.

200
00:16:13,400 --> 00:16:16,900
By the time that little twerp
steps into the ring to defend his title...

201
00:16:17,000 --> 00:16:19,700
...I'm gonna have him thinking
he's invincible.

202
00:16:19,800 --> 00:16:23,100
Then he's gonna find out
what pain and fear really mean...

203
00:16:23,200 --> 00:16:25,300
...right in front of a thousand people.

204
00:16:26,000 --> 00:16:27,400
How do you know he'll compete?

205
00:16:27,700 --> 00:16:30,400
He'll compete. Don't worry about it.
You just have fun.

206
00:16:30,500 --> 00:16:33,200
<i>Go give Mimona and her girlfriend</i>
<i>a squeeze for me.</i>

207
00:16:33,300 --> 00:16:34,500
How do you know about her?

208
00:16:34,800 --> 00:16:36,100
I know.

209
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:39,600
<i>Anything else you want?</i>

210
00:16:41,100 --> 00:16:42,300
Yeah.

211
00:16:43,900 --> 00:16:46,000
Make his knuckles bleed.

212
00:16:51,100 --> 00:16:54,300
I like that, Johnny.
I'm gonna use that.

213
00:16:56,700 --> 00:16:59,800
I'm going to be working full-time
on this from now on.

214
00:16:59,900 --> 00:17:01,000
Very good, sir.

215
00:17:01,100 --> 00:17:03,200
No, it's too nice.
I gotta look poor.

216
00:17:03,300 --> 00:17:06,000
This isn't bad. Fix the collar.
Make me look humble.

217
00:17:06,100 --> 00:17:09,100
- About the Borneo call?
- All right, but that's the last one.

218
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:11,600
For the next few weeks,
my business is revenge.

219
00:17:11,700 --> 00:17:13,500
Everything is in place, sir.

220
00:17:13,500 --> 00:17:16,200
All right,
let's see what you've got for me.

221
00:17:16,800 --> 00:17:18,400
Cute but wrong.

222
00:17:19,600 --> 00:17:21,500
It's got no character.

223
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:23,200
A truck.

224
00:17:25,200 --> 00:17:27,600
Yeah, I like it. Make sure it runs.

225
00:17:27,700 --> 00:17:28,600
Yes, sir.

226
00:17:28,700 --> 00:17:31,500
- Where are the magazines I ordered?
- Right here, sir.

227
00:17:31,600 --> 00:17:35,000
- Have a very pleasant evening, sir.
- Thank you, Margaret.

228
00:18:02,900 --> 00:18:04,400
"Karate's bad boy.

229
00:18:04,800 --> 00:18:06,100
"Mike Barnes."

230
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:15,900
Perfect.

231
00:18:25,500 --> 00:18:27,000
Mr. Miyagi, I'm home.

232
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,700
Daniel-<i>san</i>, just in time.

233
00:18:30,500 --> 00:18:32,000
How was fishing?

234
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:33,900
We find out pretty soon.

235
00:18:34,600 --> 00:18:37,100
So, how first day at college?

236
00:18:37,400 --> 00:18:38,500
College?

237
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:40,300
College...

238
00:18:41,600 --> 00:18:45,200
College is...
Well, you know college, Mr. Miyagi.

239
00:18:46,300 --> 00:18:49,100
It's a place that I didn't go to today.

240
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:51,500
What?

241
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:55,400
Mr. Miyagi,
may all your dreams come true.

242
00:18:57,300 --> 00:18:58,500
What this?

243
00:18:58,600 --> 00:19:00,800
There's only one way to find out.

244
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:05,200
All right, I'll tell you.

245
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:07,200
It's my college diploma.

246
00:19:07,300 --> 00:19:09,800
- What?
- I'm only joking.

247
00:19:10,800 --> 00:19:13,500
Daniel-<i>san</i>, you have sense humour.

248
00:19:15,700 --> 00:19:17,000
"Lease."

249
00:19:18,000 --> 00:19:20,600
For your new <i>bonsai</i> store.
Congratulations.

250
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:23,500
"One month security, two month rent."

251
00:19:23,600 --> 00:19:27,400
Yes. With just enough left over
for renovations, if we're careful.

252
00:19:28,600 --> 00:19:33,000
Daniel-<i>san</i>, thank you very much,
but cannot accept.

253
00:19:33,400 --> 00:19:36,100
But it's your dream, Mr. Miyagi.
Why not?

254
00:19:36,900 --> 00:19:40,100
Because money in pocket
was not for Miyagi dream.

255
00:19:40,700 --> 00:19:42,400
Was for college education.

256
00:19:42,400 --> 00:19:45,500
I know, just listen to me for a minute.

257
00:19:45,600 --> 00:19:49,200
I know me. I just can't take courses
to take courses.

258
00:19:49,400 --> 00:19:51,900
I'll get bored.
Once it happens, forget about it.

259
00:19:52,000 --> 00:19:53,700
It's bye-bye college.

260
00:19:53,700 --> 00:19:57,900
I've been going to school non-stop
since I'm five. I could use the break.

261
00:19:58,500 --> 00:20:00,600
- I don't know, Daniel-<i>san</i>.
- I do.

262
00:20:00,800 --> 00:20:02,900
- Just come with me a second.
- Where?

263
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:04,700
- Come with me.
- What about fish?

264
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:07,200
The fish is not going anyplace.
That fish is dead.

265
00:20:10,300 --> 00:20:12,200
What a moment!

266
00:20:12,300 --> 00:20:15,700
You are now crossing over
to the right side of the tracks.

267
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:18,200
- What that?
- That's opportunity knocking.

268
00:20:18,300 --> 00:20:20,100
Straight ahead. Right up there.

269
00:20:20,200 --> 00:20:23,000
Your dream come true,
and there's plenty of free parking.

270
00:20:23,100 --> 00:20:24,700
Right here, Mr. Miyagi.

271
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:27,900
- This place?
- This place. Wait till you see it up close.

272
00:20:32,200 --> 00:20:35,100
So, is this the opportunity
of a lifetime or what?

273
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,300
Now, I know you're worried
about this area...

274
00:20:38,400 --> 00:20:42,100
...but the landlord says
this neighbourhood is up and coming.

275
00:20:42,200 --> 00:20:46,300
We're in on the ground floor over here.
Look, a pottery shop across the street.

276
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:49,600
We could set a deal,
get some planters made up for the <i>bonsai</i>.

277
00:20:49,700 --> 00:20:52,600
Wait till you see inside, man.
This is going to be great.

278
00:20:52,700 --> 00:20:54,600
This is going to be great.

279
00:20:57,200 --> 00:20:58,500
Come on in.

280
00:21:01,900 --> 00:21:05,400
Mr. Miyagi, welcome to your dream.

281
00:21:06,500 --> 00:21:09,700
Now don't let this throw you.
Looks can be deceiving.

282
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:11,600
We have to think potential here.

283
00:21:11,700 --> 00:21:13,500
Think potential, all right?

284
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:16,000
You see all this stuff? Everything in here?

285
00:21:16,000 --> 00:21:20,100
You own it. Everything.
It's all yours. You could use this stuff.

286
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:23,500
This is good wood.
We can make shelves out of this stuff.

287
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:26,200
Back here,
I thought this would be a great spot...

288
00:21:26,300 --> 00:21:29,000
...up here, to do like a <i>bonsai</i> display.

289
00:21:29,000 --> 00:21:32,600
All those pine trees you have?
We could show them in different stages.

290
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:35,000
You know, the possibilities are endless.

291
00:21:35,100 --> 00:21:38,600
Over here, right,
I thought this would be a great spot...

292
00:21:38,700 --> 00:21:40,300
...for a little work area.

293
00:21:40,400 --> 00:21:46,000
Over here we got like a <i>bonsai</i> hospital.
The little guys get sick. Take care of them.

294
00:21:46,100 --> 00:21:48,700
I work for free. And I thought of a name.

295
00:21:48,700 --> 00:21:49,900
Check it out.

296
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:52,300
"Mr. Miyagi's Little Trees."

297
00:21:52,700 --> 00:21:55,000
Simple, direct, catchy.

298
00:21:55,100 --> 00:21:57,800
It doesn't look it now,
but this place is a gold mine.

299
00:21:57,900 --> 00:22:01,500
I know you can make it work, Mr. Miyagi.
If anyone can, you can.

300
00:22:04,200 --> 00:22:06,800
What did I do? Did I forget something?

301
00:22:08,400 --> 00:22:10,100
Well, what did I miss?

302
00:22:10,200 --> 00:22:12,700
Your name on lease, next to mine.

303
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:16,300
- Partner.
- Partner?

304
00:22:17,300 --> 00:22:19,900
Yes! Mr. Miyagi, this is gonna be great.

305
00:22:32,700 --> 00:22:34,200
You're welcome.

306
00:22:37,200 --> 00:22:38,400
What?

307
00:22:39,600 --> 00:22:41,400
Don't bullshit me.

308
00:22:41,600 --> 00:22:43,700
What do you mean
you can't dump it in Borneo?

309
00:22:43,700 --> 00:22:45,900
Who in Borneo
knows what chloride sludge is?

310
00:22:46,000 --> 00:22:47,100
Just do it!

311
00:22:47,400 --> 00:22:48,600
Do it!

312
00:22:48,900 --> 00:22:50,600
Call me when it's dumped.

313
00:22:50,700 --> 00:22:52,100
Where were we, Margaret?

314
00:22:52,200 --> 00:22:55,300
"And, in conclusion,
I reject your final offer.

315
00:22:55,400 --> 00:22:59,900
"If you proceed,
I'll sue your collective asses accordingly."

316
00:23:00,100 --> 00:23:02,900
Best to Lorna and the kids. Sincerely...

317
00:23:03,900 --> 00:23:05,100
Yeah?

318
00:23:05,400 --> 00:23:07,000
Good, bring him in.

319
00:23:07,100 --> 00:23:08,200
What else?

320
00:23:08,400 --> 00:23:11,800
The grand jury.
What do you intend to do about them?

321
00:23:11,900 --> 00:23:13,400
Bribe them, as usual.

322
00:23:14,200 --> 00:23:15,700
Lighten up, Margaret.

323
00:23:15,900 --> 00:23:18,300
- Who's the DA on the case?
- Mr. Cole.

324
00:23:18,400 --> 00:23:19,500
Good.

325
00:23:19,600 --> 00:23:23,200
Let's invite Willie to dinner Tuesday night.
We'll have his favourite.

326
00:23:23,300 --> 00:23:25,000
- Poached salmon.
- Very well.

327
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:26,300
Mr. Silver?

328
00:23:27,000 --> 00:23:29,300
You must be Mike Barnes. Welcome to LA.

329
00:23:29,300 --> 00:23:31,600
Thank you for bringing me down,
Mr. Silver.

330
00:23:31,700 --> 00:23:33,600
Milos, call the boys.

331
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:36,500
This place is intense.

332
00:23:36,600 --> 00:23:39,000
- Consider it home.
- Thanks.

333
00:23:39,500 --> 00:23:41,100
Snake, Dennis.

334
00:23:41,200 --> 00:23:42,200
Mike Barnes.

335
00:23:42,300 --> 00:23:46,100
Dennis will take care of your training.
Snake takes care of everything else.

336
00:23:46,200 --> 00:23:49,900
If you're looking to be a bad boy in LA,
Snake's the boy to be bad with.

337
00:23:49,900 --> 00:23:51,300
You know it.

338
00:23:52,200 --> 00:23:54,700
You get a weekly draw and a car.
Any questions?

339
00:23:54,800 --> 00:23:57,100
Remember on the phone you said
if I come here...

340
00:23:57,200 --> 00:24:00,100
...and I beat this LaRusso
in the All Valley Tournament...

341
00:24:00,200 --> 00:24:03,300
...that you'd give me 25 percent ownership
in your new <i>dojo</i>s?

342
00:24:03,500 --> 00:24:05,700
Which I think is more than generous.

343
00:24:05,700 --> 00:24:08,000
But I've been giving it some thought.

344
00:24:08,100 --> 00:24:11,900
For me to do my absolute best,
which is what I want to do for you...

345
00:24:12,000 --> 00:24:14,400
...l'm afraid I'm gonna need 50 percent.

346
00:24:16,200 --> 00:24:17,700
Fifty percent?

347
00:24:18,700 --> 00:24:22,000
Well, I don't know
if I can afford more than 35.

348
00:24:23,900 --> 00:24:27,000
I understand. I guess I'd better get going.

349
00:24:27,100 --> 00:24:29,100
It was nice meeting everybody.

350
00:24:30,700 --> 00:24:34,100
- Do you fight as hard as you negotiate?
- Harder.

351
00:24:34,100 --> 00:24:35,700
You got your 50 percent.

352
00:24:35,800 --> 00:24:38,600
- And I get that in writing?
- By noon today.

353
00:24:39,300 --> 00:24:43,000
You just bought yourself a champion.

354
00:24:43,100 --> 00:24:44,900
You remember that.

355
00:24:45,800 --> 00:24:48,200
- Snake, show him to his room.
- Yes, sir.

356
00:24:49,000 --> 00:24:51,900
See you later, Mike.
Milos, my blue pinstripe.

357
00:24:56,200 --> 00:24:58,000
So, what do you think?

358
00:24:58,100 --> 00:24:59,600
He's obnoxious.

359
00:25:00,700 --> 00:25:02,500
Yeah, he's perfect.

360
00:25:09,100 --> 00:25:12,300
Very good. This make special <i>bonsai</i>.

361
00:25:12,400 --> 00:25:14,800
You really see a <i>bonsai</i> in here?

362
00:25:15,300 --> 00:25:16,300
Where?

363
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:17,500
Inside.

364
00:25:17,600 --> 00:25:18,900
Inside?

365
00:25:19,000 --> 00:25:20,900
Hello, any <i>bonsai</i> in here?

366
00:25:21,400 --> 00:25:25,000
Daniel-<i>san</i>, not inside. Inside you.

367
00:25:25,100 --> 00:25:27,600
Same place your karate come from.

368
00:25:27,700 --> 00:25:29,700
But my karate comes from you.

369
00:25:31,200 --> 00:25:34,300
Only root karate come from Miyagi.

370
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:40,600
Just like <i>bonsai</i> choose own way grow.
Because the root is strong.

371
00:25:42,100 --> 00:25:45,400
You choose own way.
Do karate same reason.

372
00:25:45,600 --> 00:25:47,700
Yeah, but I do it your way.

373
00:25:48,600 --> 00:25:51,500
One day you do own way.

374
00:25:58,200 --> 00:26:02,000
Remember what you said before about
<i>bonsai</i> being free to grow as they choose?

375
00:26:02,100 --> 00:26:04,200
All <i>bonsai</i> aren't free to choose.

376
00:26:04,300 --> 00:26:08,100
We tell them how to grow
by using clippers and then the wire.

377
00:26:08,700 --> 00:26:12,200
But, Daniel-<i>san</i>,
our <i>bonsai</i> not true <i>bonsai</i>.

378
00:26:12,400 --> 00:26:15,800
True <i>bonsai</i> grow wild. Very rare.

379
00:26:15,900 --> 00:26:17,300
You ever seen any?

380
00:26:17,900 --> 00:26:19,000
Okinawa.

381
00:26:19,100 --> 00:26:20,500
What about here?

382
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:22,000
I only know of one.

383
00:26:23,300 --> 00:26:25,100
What did it do, immigrate?

384
00:26:26,100 --> 00:26:30,100
With Miyagi.
Only thing Miyagi bring from Okinawa.

385
00:26:30,300 --> 00:26:32,100
Where's the tree now?

386
00:26:33,200 --> 00:26:34,300
There.

387
00:26:34,400 --> 00:26:36,100
Devil's Caldron.

388
00:26:38,800 --> 00:26:40,200
Devil's Caldron?

389
00:26:41,400 --> 00:26:43,700
No can see <i>bonsai</i> from here.

390
00:26:44,400 --> 00:26:47,500
Good place. Very safe. Nobody bother.

391
00:26:47,600 --> 00:26:50,200
Why did you put it
in such a hard place to get to?

392
00:26:50,300 --> 00:26:53,300
True original <i>bonsai</i>
worth many thousand dollar.

393
00:26:53,900 --> 00:26:57,300
Come, time learn special
Miyagi-family <i>kata</i>.

394
00:26:57,400 --> 00:26:58,800
Now you ready.

395
00:26:58,800 --> 00:27:03,500
Like all <i>bonsai</i> found in tree,
all karate found in this <i>kata</i>.

396
00:27:03,600 --> 00:27:06,100
Come, together we do <i>kata</i>.

397
00:28:31,100 --> 00:28:32,800
Hi, Mr. Miyagi.

398
00:28:32,800 --> 00:28:35,800
I brought this tree,
the one you were working on this morning.

399
00:28:35,900 --> 00:28:38,200
I thought you might want
to give it another try.

400
00:28:38,300 --> 00:28:39,100
Thank you.

401
00:28:39,200 --> 00:28:42,300
A change of scenery
might bring what's inside outside.

402
00:28:42,400 --> 00:28:44,700
- Where should I put it?
- Over here.

403
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:46,600
Very good.

404
00:28:46,700 --> 00:28:50,100
You've done a lot of work here.
This place is bigger than I thought.

405
00:28:50,200 --> 00:28:52,700
- There's your charcoal.
- Thank you.

406
00:28:53,900 --> 00:28:55,000
Perfect.

407
00:28:57,100 --> 00:28:59,200
I hope you don't mind...

408
00:29:00,700 --> 00:29:03,000
...but I opened that letter.

409
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:06,100
The one that came today
from the All Valley Tournament.

410
00:29:06,200 --> 00:29:08,200
There's a new rule this year.

411
00:29:09,400 --> 00:29:11,800
- Would you like to read about it?
- No.

412
00:29:12,400 --> 00:29:15,500
That's okay because I got it memorised.
It says:

413
00:29:15,600 --> 00:29:17,000
"Under the new rules...

414
00:29:17,100 --> 00:29:20,400
"...the defending champion
only needs to fight in the final match."

415
00:29:20,500 --> 00:29:23,900
Isn't that great?
That limits my fights to just one.

416
00:29:24,300 --> 00:29:27,400
That's better
than what I had to put up with last year.

417
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:30,400
And let's face it, it's another year.

418
00:29:30,500 --> 00:29:33,200
It's a year later.
I'm a lot more experienced.

419
00:29:33,500 --> 00:29:36,700
So I think we should
seriously reconsider this.

420
00:29:37,000 --> 00:29:38,900
- Right?
- Wrong!

421
00:29:39,000 --> 00:29:40,200
Wrong?

422
00:29:40,400 --> 00:29:43,400
Should consider get
new pot for <i>bonsai</i>.

423
00:29:43,800 --> 00:29:48,000
I don't know what the big deal is.
I mean, what is your problem with this?

424
00:29:50,500 --> 00:29:54,400
If karate used defend honour,
defend a life...

425
00:29:54,900 --> 00:29:57,200
...karate means something.

426
00:29:58,100 --> 00:30:01,400
If karate used defend plastic metal trophy...

427
00:30:02,300 --> 00:30:04,700
...karate no mean nothing.

428
00:30:07,100 --> 00:30:08,600
Understand?

429
00:30:09,400 --> 00:30:10,700
I wish I did.

430
00:30:13,000 --> 00:30:16,400
Go find a nice pot for <i>bonsai</i> across street.

431
00:30:23,000 --> 00:30:24,500
Here's your pen.

432
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:26,900
Before I forget.

433
00:30:29,700 --> 00:30:34,200
And if you have a minute,
just in case you change your mind...

434
00:30:34,300 --> 00:30:35,900
...here's the application.

435
00:30:36,000 --> 00:30:37,100
Okay?

436
00:30:38,800 --> 00:30:41,700
It's no rush.
I mean, it says at the bottom...

437
00:30:41,800 --> 00:30:45,000
We have a couple of weeks
before we have to send it in.

438
00:30:45,900 --> 00:30:49,400
I'm sorry if I made it seem
like we had to do it today.

439
00:30:51,200 --> 00:30:53,000
We have some time.

440
00:31:08,500 --> 00:31:09,800
Hello?

441
00:31:10,800 --> 00:31:13,000
Hi. Could you turn that off?

442
00:31:13,300 --> 00:31:14,300
Sure.

443
00:31:14,500 --> 00:31:15,700
Thanks.

444
00:31:15,800 --> 00:31:18,300
Hang on, I'm almost finished.

445
00:31:18,300 --> 00:31:19,500
That's okay.

446
00:31:19,600 --> 00:31:21,600
It's okay. Take your time.

447
00:31:23,100 --> 00:31:24,500
That's pretty cool.

448
00:31:24,600 --> 00:31:25,900
Thanks.

449
00:31:26,300 --> 00:31:28,100
So, what can I do for you?

450
00:31:28,200 --> 00:31:31,500
Actually, I was looking to buy some pots.

451
00:31:32,000 --> 00:31:33,700
Yeah, what size?

452
00:31:37,300 --> 00:31:39,900
This would be good. Like this.

453
00:31:40,500 --> 00:31:43,800
They're for <i>bonsai</i> trees.
We're opening a shop across the street.

454
00:31:43,900 --> 00:31:46,000
Great. Welcome to the neighbourhood.

455
00:31:46,000 --> 00:31:47,200
Thanks.

456
00:31:47,800 --> 00:31:49,500
Yeah, I love <i>bonsai</i>.

457
00:31:49,700 --> 00:31:52,000
They're so perfect, you know?

458
00:31:52,200 --> 00:31:55,700
Maybe when we get our trees in
you could come visit the shop.

459
00:31:55,800 --> 00:31:57,500
And meet my partner, too.

460
00:31:57,600 --> 00:31:59,600
I haven't even really met you yet.

461
00:31:59,700 --> 00:32:01,300
I'm sorry.

462
00:32:01,800 --> 00:32:04,400
- Daniel LaRusso.
- Jessica Andrews. Hi.

463
00:32:04,500 --> 00:32:07,000
Hi. Is that you in that...

464
00:32:07,400 --> 00:32:08,900
Yep, that's me.

465
00:32:09,000 --> 00:32:11,700
What happened to the guy
who lost his head?

466
00:32:12,600 --> 00:32:15,600
Elizabeth Anne Rooney happened to him.
The traitor.

467
00:32:15,900 --> 00:32:17,400
The pots?

468
00:32:17,500 --> 00:32:19,400
You know what we could do?

469
00:32:21,200 --> 00:32:24,700
Could you put like a <i>bonsai</i> tree
on the side of the pot?

470
00:32:24,800 --> 00:32:27,800
- It's sort of like our trademark.
- Like embossed?

471
00:32:27,900 --> 00:32:30,700
Right on the side.
I'll draw a picture of it for you.

472
00:32:30,800 --> 00:32:32,800
That would be great.

473
00:32:32,900 --> 00:32:37,100
- Jessica, come on. I'm late, hurry up.
- Listen, I got to deal with this guy.

474
00:32:37,800 --> 00:32:40,000
Thanks, I'll see you soon then.

475
00:32:40,400 --> 00:32:41,500
How soon?

476
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:44,300
How soon? Well, I don't know.

477
00:32:45,100 --> 00:32:47,100
- Busy tonight?
- No.

478
00:32:47,100 --> 00:32:48,200
No?

479
00:32:48,300 --> 00:32:51,800
Well, then I'll see you tonight.
If that's okay with you?

480
00:32:51,900 --> 00:32:53,600
Okay. About 7:00?

481
00:32:53,800 --> 00:32:55,700
Well, sure. 7:00 is good.

482
00:32:55,700 --> 00:32:58,900
I just live right upstairs,
so go around the side, okay?

483
00:32:59,400 --> 00:33:02,400
- I'll see you around the side, 7:00.
- Bye-bye.

484
00:33:02,500 --> 00:33:05,300
Charles is going to get angry.
Open up the gate.

485
00:33:18,500 --> 00:33:20,100
You found it, huh?

486
00:33:21,900 --> 00:33:23,300
Thanks to you.

487
00:33:23,400 --> 00:33:25,900
Thanks to me? I didn't do anything.

488
00:33:26,100 --> 00:33:27,800
That looks great.

489
00:33:29,100 --> 00:33:30,900
You find something?

490
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:35,100
Yeah. Yeah, actually I did.
I found a date.

491
00:33:35,200 --> 00:33:38,300
You didn't send me over there
just to look at pots, did you?

492
00:33:38,400 --> 00:33:39,900
Yeah, I knew it.

493
00:33:42,900 --> 00:33:44,800
Did you sign it?

494
00:33:46,200 --> 00:33:47,700
You didn't sign it.

495
00:33:48,200 --> 00:33:49,200
No.

496
00:33:53,800 --> 00:33:57,900
I understand your feelings on this.
But you have to understand mine.

497
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:00,500
This is the biggest thing
I've ever done in my life.

498
00:34:00,500 --> 00:34:03,700
I'm proud of this title.
Why can't I defend it?

499
00:34:04,000 --> 00:34:06,500
Daniel-<i>san</i>,
you no look answer Miyagi.

500
00:34:07,400 --> 00:34:13,300
Just like a <i>bonsai</i> live inside the tree,
answer live inside of you.

501
00:34:14,500 --> 00:34:17,800
The only thing living inside me right now
is a lot of confusion.

502
00:34:17,900 --> 00:34:20,000
I have the chance
to be the champion again.

503
00:34:20,100 --> 00:34:23,700
- All I have to do is put my signature to it.
- Or match to it.

504
00:34:24,600 --> 00:34:26,000
A match to it?

505
00:34:27,600 --> 00:34:30,600
Then you watch confusion disappear
with the smoke.

506
00:36:15,300 --> 00:36:17,100
"442nd."

507
00:37:38,500 --> 00:37:40,100
What are you doing here?

508
00:37:40,800 --> 00:37:42,500
- Forget something.
- What?

509
00:37:42,900 --> 00:37:46,000
For shop. Bring good luck.

510
00:37:46,500 --> 00:37:49,300
Well, I hope it brings good customers, too.

511
00:37:50,200 --> 00:37:52,100
Daniel-<i>san</i> look good.

512
00:37:52,200 --> 00:37:54,600
Thanks for the shirt. I love it, man.

513
00:37:55,700 --> 00:37:57,000
What doing?

514
00:37:57,100 --> 00:38:01,700
I've been thinking about what you said,
and I decided to take your advice.

515
00:38:01,700 --> 00:38:04,400
I'm going to let my confusion
go up in smoke.

516
00:38:04,500 --> 00:38:06,000
I'm not entering the tournament.

517
00:38:06,100 --> 00:38:09,300
I want my karate and your karate
to mean something.

518
00:38:14,300 --> 00:38:16,200
Good decision, Daniel-<i>san</i>.

519
00:38:16,700 --> 00:38:19,700
This way no more bruises.
Save money on Band-Aid.

520
00:38:19,800 --> 00:38:23,600
Get out of here.
They never laid a hand on me last year.

521
00:38:23,600 --> 00:38:25,500
Just an elbow, a few feet.

522
00:38:26,400 --> 00:38:30,200
I'll never forget that knee to the groin.
That was interesting.

523
00:38:30,400 --> 00:38:32,500
I'll see you later, Mr. Miyagi.

524
00:38:36,800 --> 00:38:38,600
- Hi.
- Hi.

525
00:38:38,700 --> 00:38:40,500
So, you all set to go?

526
00:38:42,500 --> 00:38:44,800
First I gotta tell you this.

527
00:38:47,800 --> 00:38:51,100
After you hear this,
you just might change your mind.

528
00:38:51,700 --> 00:38:54,000
What do you have, poison oak?

529
00:38:54,100 --> 00:38:55,600
A boyfriend.

530
00:38:55,800 --> 00:39:00,300
You see, he was in the headless picture.
You know, we broke up two months ago.

531
00:39:00,500 --> 00:39:02,900
You mean Elizabeth Anne Rooney...

532
00:39:03,000 --> 00:39:08,000
We were both a little dumb about it,
but we've been talking on the phone.

533
00:39:08,100 --> 00:39:11,200
I don't know, we're gonna give it
another try when I go home.

534
00:39:11,200 --> 00:39:13,900
- Where's home?
- Columbus. Ohio.

535
00:39:14,800 --> 00:39:17,400
Yeah, I'm gonna go back
after Thanksgiving.

536
00:39:17,500 --> 00:39:20,000
- I just didn't want to lead you on.
- No.

537
00:39:20,100 --> 00:39:21,800
I did come on kind of strong.

538
00:39:22,000 --> 00:39:25,200
No, don't worry about it. It's refreshing.
We could go Dutch.

539
00:39:25,200 --> 00:39:26,700
That sounds great.

540
00:39:27,900 --> 00:39:30,300
It's just that I've been here
for two months...

541
00:39:30,300 --> 00:39:33,700
...with absolutely nothing to do
and I haven't even met any friends.

542
00:39:33,800 --> 00:39:35,400
Meet your first friend.

543
00:39:35,500 --> 00:39:36,800
All right.

544
00:39:36,900 --> 00:39:38,400
Yeah, this is wild.

545
00:39:38,500 --> 00:39:40,400
Wait till he hears about this one.

546
00:39:40,500 --> 00:39:41,600
Who?

547
00:39:41,700 --> 00:39:45,100
Mr. Miyagi. He's my partner.
You wanna meet him?

548
00:39:45,100 --> 00:39:46,300
Yeah, why not?

549
00:39:46,400 --> 00:39:48,600
You are about to meet the greatest guy.

550
00:39:48,700 --> 00:39:52,800
This guy, he's funny, he's smart.
You got a problem, he's got the answer.

551
00:39:52,900 --> 00:39:54,500
He's like no one you'll ever meet.

552
00:39:54,600 --> 00:39:56,900
On top of that,
he happens to be my best friend.

553
00:39:57,000 --> 00:39:58,400
Why do you call him "mister"?

554
00:39:58,400 --> 00:39:59,600
Mr. Miyagi.

555
00:40:00,200 --> 00:40:03,400
Meet Jessica Andrews from
Columbus, Ohio, and across the street.

556
00:40:03,500 --> 00:40:05,500
This is Mr. Miyagi
from Okinawa and Reseda.

557
00:40:05,600 --> 00:40:07,500
- How do you do?
- Hi.

558
00:40:07,500 --> 00:40:10,500
- Jessica's gonna make those pots for us.
- Very good.

559
00:40:10,600 --> 00:40:13,500
- Welcome to the neighbourhood.
- Thank you very much.

560
00:40:13,600 --> 00:40:15,300
How's it going so far? Good?

561
00:40:15,400 --> 00:40:19,600
I never know retirement
mean such hard work.

562
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:22,900
- You like to see inside shop?
- Yeah, I'd love to.

563
00:40:23,000 --> 00:40:25,600
Partner show you around.
Don't forget lock up.

564
00:40:25,600 --> 00:40:26,800
No, I won't.

565
00:40:26,900 --> 00:40:29,900
- Good night. Nice to meet you.
- Nice to meet you, too.

566
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:32,700
- I'll see you later.
- Bye-bye.

567
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:37,200
- You see why I call him "mister"?
- Yeah. He's nice.

568
00:40:37,300 --> 00:40:39,200
He's the best. Come on in.

569
00:40:42,500 --> 00:40:43,600
What's this?

570
00:40:43,700 --> 00:40:47,000
That's Mr. Miyagi's.
He brought it for good luck.

571
00:40:47,100 --> 00:40:49,200
What do you think?
It is going to be great.

572
00:40:49,300 --> 00:40:52,000
- Yeah, it is.
- It needs a little work, but...

573
00:40:52,000 --> 00:40:53,400
So where'd you meet him?

574
00:40:53,500 --> 00:40:56,800
I met him when I moved out here.
He started teaching me karate.

575
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:58,100
Karate?

576
00:40:58,300 --> 00:41:00,100
- You do karate?
- Yeah, I do.

577
00:41:00,900 --> 00:41:03,400
He doesn't really look like
the karate-teacher type.

578
00:41:03,500 --> 00:41:05,300
He doesn't act like it either.

579
00:41:05,300 --> 00:41:08,200
Half the time he teaches me stuff,
I don't know what it is.

580
00:41:08,300 --> 00:41:09,400
What do you mean?

581
00:41:09,500 --> 00:41:12,100
It's like that vase
you were making this morning.

582
00:41:12,100 --> 00:41:14,500
He'll make a whole karate lesson
out of that.

583
00:41:14,600 --> 00:41:16,200
No, I'm not kidding.

584
00:41:16,200 --> 00:41:18,900
Show me how you were making that...

585
00:41:18,900 --> 00:41:22,200
- You go up and then you go down.
- Okay, now you do that.

586
00:41:22,300 --> 00:41:23,700
Okay, go up.

587
00:41:24,500 --> 00:41:27,100
Now, okay, right, see just like that.
Now go down.

588
00:41:27,200 --> 00:41:29,600
Okay, now do that again. Go up.
I'm a mugger.

589
00:41:29,700 --> 00:41:32,300
I'm gonna grab you,
now grab the back of my head.

590
00:41:32,400 --> 00:41:34,500
Then pull down and bring your knee up.

591
00:41:34,500 --> 00:41:36,000
Room for one more down there?

592
00:41:37,100 --> 00:41:38,900
- What are you doing? We're not open.
- The door was.

593
00:41:39,000 --> 00:41:40,600
I meant for business, pal.

594
00:41:40,700 --> 00:41:44,300
I didn't come here for business.
Came here to talk to you.

595
00:41:44,400 --> 00:41:47,100
We heard you weren't entering
the All Valley this year.

596
00:41:47,100 --> 00:41:49,100
Is that true, Daniel?

597
00:41:49,200 --> 00:41:51,000
- Where'd you hear that?
- Is it true?

598
00:41:51,100 --> 00:41:52,700
Yeah, that's true. So what?

599
00:41:52,800 --> 00:41:56,400
- We'd like you to reconsider.
- Is that why you guys came down here?

600
00:41:56,500 --> 00:42:00,600
- I need your title.
- Then enter the tournament and go for it.

601
00:42:00,700 --> 00:42:03,100
Maybe you didn't hear me.
I need your title.

602
00:42:03,200 --> 00:42:05,700
You don't enter
and that effects my financial future.

603
00:42:05,700 --> 00:42:07,600
I won't let that happen. Get it?

604
00:42:07,700 --> 00:42:10,200
I have nothing to prove.
I have no reason to fight.

605
00:42:10,200 --> 00:42:13,000
I do. I got some money to make.
Give me the application.

606
00:42:13,100 --> 00:42:14,900
Forget it. I'm not going to fight...

607
00:42:15,000 --> 00:42:15,900
Sign it!

608
00:42:21,100 --> 00:42:22,600
You sign it, man!

609
00:42:22,700 --> 00:42:25,100
Come on, man! Right now!

610
00:42:25,200 --> 00:42:26,300
Let's go, punk!

611
00:42:26,400 --> 00:42:29,400
Let LaRusso sleep on it.
Come on. Mike!

612
00:42:29,500 --> 00:42:32,200
Yeah, you sleep on it.

613
00:42:32,600 --> 00:42:35,800
And you can dream about me.

614
00:42:36,500 --> 00:42:37,700
You slimeball.

615
00:42:37,800 --> 00:42:41,600
Slimeball? That's cute.
Did your mother teach you that?

616
00:42:41,700 --> 00:42:43,200
Come on, Mike.

617
00:42:43,900 --> 00:42:47,900
You'll have to excuse him.
He's usually a very mellow guy.

618
00:42:48,300 --> 00:42:49,500
See you later.

619
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:52,800
Do you know those creeps?

620
00:42:53,400 --> 00:42:54,500
No.

621
00:42:54,900 --> 00:42:57,300
And I wanna keep it that way.

622
00:43:20,400 --> 00:43:21,700
Excuse me.

623
00:43:22,100 --> 00:43:23,500
Mr. Miyagi?

624
00:43:25,800 --> 00:43:27,700
My name is Terry Silver.

625
00:43:27,900 --> 00:43:30,500
My master is Kim San Jang
of South Korea.

626
00:43:30,600 --> 00:43:33,000
My teacher sends his respects.

627
00:43:35,900 --> 00:43:40,000
John Kreese of the Cobra Kai <i>dojo</i>
was our school's number one student.

628
00:43:40,700 --> 00:43:43,000
Word reached us in Korea
only two months ago...

629
00:43:43,100 --> 00:43:45,600
...about what happened last year
at the tournament.

630
00:43:45,700 --> 00:43:49,600
My teacher sends his apologies
for John Kreese's dishonourable actions.

631
00:43:53,000 --> 00:43:54,600
Accept apology.

632
00:43:56,100 --> 00:43:58,900
I was sent here
to help John regain balance.

633
00:43:59,800 --> 00:44:02,000
Hope you can be successful.

634
00:44:02,400 --> 00:44:04,900
Unfortunately, I arrived too late.

635
00:44:05,800 --> 00:44:07,800
I buried John last week.

636
00:44:10,200 --> 00:44:11,700
He's dead? What happened?

637
00:44:11,800 --> 00:44:15,500
His doctor said it was cardiac arrest,
but I knew John better than anyone.

638
00:44:15,600 --> 00:44:17,000
Karate was his life.

639
00:44:17,100 --> 00:44:21,000
And after he lost all his students,
it just broke his heart.

640
00:44:21,500 --> 00:44:25,000
John was a hero.
He wasn't always like what you saw.

641
00:44:25,500 --> 00:44:27,800
He saved my life in Vietnam.

642
00:44:28,800 --> 00:44:31,100
War does something to a man.

643
00:44:33,200 --> 00:44:35,900
You had to have been there
to know what I mean.

644
00:44:35,900 --> 00:44:37,300
Have been.

645
00:44:38,500 --> 00:44:39,900
Do know.

646
00:44:40,900 --> 00:44:42,200
442nd?

647
00:44:44,300 --> 00:44:45,400
Man!

648
00:44:45,900 --> 00:44:48,300
More medals of honour
came out of the 442nd...

649
00:44:48,400 --> 00:44:50,700
...than all World War II put together.

650
00:44:50,800 --> 00:44:52,900
I bet you've been there.

651
00:44:53,700 --> 00:44:56,100
Is this your student? The champion?

652
00:44:56,400 --> 00:44:57,500
Yeah.

653
00:44:57,600 --> 00:44:59,700
Our apologies to you, too.

654
00:45:01,200 --> 00:45:04,000
John had vowed
to come and apologise himself.

655
00:45:04,400 --> 00:45:05,800
He planned...

656
00:45:09,400 --> 00:45:12,700
Look, I'm sorry.
I'm sorry to interrupt your training.

657
00:45:14,100 --> 00:45:15,800
Mr. Silver...

658
00:45:17,700 --> 00:45:20,400
...very sorry to hear about death of friend.

659
00:45:21,400 --> 00:45:22,900
Me, too.

660
00:45:24,400 --> 00:45:25,800
Thank you.

661
00:45:33,200 --> 00:45:35,100
God, that's too bad.

662
00:45:36,500 --> 00:45:38,300
Too bad, Daniel-<i>san</i>.

663
00:45:39,100 --> 00:45:41,100
Come, we continue <i>kata</i>.

664
00:45:55,600 --> 00:45:56,600
Hello?

665
00:45:57,500 --> 00:45:59,300
- Eat yet?
- No, I haven't.

666
00:45:59,400 --> 00:46:02,700
I was supposed to dine with my Aunt Pat.
She owns the shop.

667
00:46:02,800 --> 00:46:07,700
She had to do some things, so I got stuck
with all this macaroni and cheese.

668
00:46:07,700 --> 00:46:10,900
Macaroni and cheese?
You know what I like!

669
00:46:11,000 --> 00:46:13,000
I grew up on macaroni and cheese.

670
00:46:13,100 --> 00:46:15,900
I never say no
when it comes to macaroni and cheese.

671
00:46:16,000 --> 00:46:18,100
- Here, have a seat.
- Thanks.

672
00:46:18,200 --> 00:46:20,400
I used to eat this stuff by the ton.

673
00:46:20,800 --> 00:46:23,300
I want you to try this, okay?
And be honest.

674
00:46:23,300 --> 00:46:24,300
Okay.

675
00:46:28,100 --> 00:46:31,300
On a scale of one to ten, I'd give it as...

676
00:46:32,700 --> 00:46:33,800
...eleven.

677
00:46:34,100 --> 00:46:36,000
Let's eat. I'm starved.

678
00:46:36,300 --> 00:46:38,200
I hope you like this.

679
00:46:38,400 --> 00:46:41,600
I'm not sure if this is
exactly what you wanted, but...

680
00:46:42,800 --> 00:46:44,700
Hey, this came out great.

681
00:46:44,900 --> 00:46:47,400
- Look at the tree. You got it just right.
- Good.

682
00:46:47,500 --> 00:46:50,700
- Wait until Mr. Miyagi sees it.
- Do you think he'll like it?

683
00:46:50,700 --> 00:46:52,700
Like it? He's gonna love it. Here.

684
00:46:52,800 --> 00:46:55,200
- I have something for you.
- For me?

685
00:46:56,800 --> 00:46:58,300
What is this?

686
00:47:00,000 --> 00:47:01,700
The Down Stairs? What is that?

687
00:47:01,800 --> 00:47:05,000
It's a dance club. Yeah, it's great.
It's got live music.

688
00:47:05,100 --> 00:47:07,800
It's for the night before you go back home.

689
00:47:07,800 --> 00:47:10,600
I figured it would be
a nice going-away present.

690
00:47:10,800 --> 00:47:13,100
Daniel, that is so sweet.

691
00:47:15,500 --> 00:47:19,000
Come on, guys. This isn't funny anymore.
Come on, turn on the lights.

692
00:47:19,100 --> 00:47:22,300
Danny, I hope you got some good news
for my friend Mike here.

693
00:47:22,400 --> 00:47:24,100
- I hope so too, Daniel.
- I told you.

694
00:47:24,200 --> 00:47:26,900
I can't help you. Forget about it.
Where are you going?

695
00:47:27,000 --> 00:47:28,900
You haven't signed the application yet.

696
00:47:29,000 --> 00:47:31,500
I'm not signing the application.
I won't compete.

697
00:47:31,600 --> 00:47:33,400
Take your friends and get out of here.

698
00:47:33,500 --> 00:47:35,700
Dennis, he didn't sign it yet.

699
00:47:41,500 --> 00:47:44,100
Come on, guys.
This is getting out of hand now.

700
00:47:44,200 --> 00:47:47,000
- I'm not signing the application.
- Sure you are.

701
00:47:47,100 --> 00:47:49,800
I'm not going to be there.
You're wasting your time.

702
00:47:49,900 --> 00:47:51,500
- Take off, all right?
- You take off!

703
00:47:51,600 --> 00:47:54,400
- Come on, Dennis, take him out!
- Put his eye out!

704
00:47:54,600 --> 00:47:56,300
Come on!

705
00:48:05,700 --> 00:48:08,100
Come on, punk!
Let's see what you've got!

706
00:48:08,100 --> 00:48:09,700
Nice kick. Not bad.

707
00:48:09,800 --> 00:48:12,000
Better. Good, but not good enough.

708
00:48:15,400 --> 00:48:17,000
Come on, get up!

709
00:48:17,600 --> 00:48:19,600
Why are you being so stubborn?

710
00:48:20,500 --> 00:48:21,700
Don't do that!

711
00:48:25,100 --> 00:48:28,900
I am running out of patience.
Now sign it and let's get on with it.

712
00:48:29,600 --> 00:48:31,000
Stop it!

713
00:48:33,300 --> 00:48:34,500
It's your ass!

714
00:48:35,000 --> 00:48:36,600
Just get out of here!

715
00:48:37,300 --> 00:48:40,100
- Save it for the tournament!
- Nail him!

716
00:48:40,100 --> 00:48:42,500
Mike, come on, let's get out of here!

717
00:48:43,700 --> 00:48:45,200
Come on, old man!

718
00:48:48,700 --> 00:48:50,300
Mike, let's go!

719
00:48:51,800 --> 00:48:53,600
Let's go! You wimp!

720
00:48:56,400 --> 00:48:58,900
I'll be back, LaRusso.
I'm gonna get you.

721
00:48:58,900 --> 00:49:00,900
You're finished!

722
00:49:01,100 --> 00:49:03,400
You can't watch him forever, Buddha-head.

723
00:49:13,300 --> 00:49:15,300
So, Daniel-<i>san</i>, time take Jessica home.

724
00:49:15,400 --> 00:49:17,000
Yeah. Jessica, you all right?

725
00:49:17,100 --> 00:49:19,300
Yeah. I just want to lie down.

726
00:49:32,700 --> 00:49:35,000
I can't believe you're singing.

727
00:49:35,400 --> 00:49:36,400
Forget it.

728
00:49:40,700 --> 00:49:42,200
Feel lucky, Daniel-<i>san</i>.

729
00:49:42,300 --> 00:49:44,300
Lucky? How could you feel lucky?

730
00:49:44,400 --> 00:49:48,000
Feel lucky. <i>Bonsai</i> tree not in shop.
Safe at home.

731
00:49:48,300 --> 00:49:51,500
That makes us real lucky.
I never felt luckier in my life.

732
00:49:51,600 --> 00:49:54,200
Daniel-<i>san</i>, we can rebuild the shop.

733
00:49:54,500 --> 00:49:56,300
Cannot rebuild stock.

734
00:49:58,800 --> 00:50:03,300
We sell a few trees, fix <i>shoji</i> screen,
start over again.

735
00:50:04,200 --> 00:50:07,600
What if those guys come back again?
What are we going to do then?

736
00:50:07,700 --> 00:50:10,100
If they come back,
what are we going to do?

737
00:50:10,200 --> 00:50:12,900
Just tell me,
what do we do if they come back?

738
00:50:17,700 --> 00:50:19,100
Sing happy song.

739
00:50:37,000 --> 00:50:39,700
Where are the trees?
Where'd you put the trees?

740
00:50:42,900 --> 00:50:44,400
They stole them!

741
00:50:45,600 --> 00:50:48,600
I can't believe it. They stole the trees.
Don't they get it?

742
00:50:48,700 --> 00:50:52,400
I'm not going to sign this thing.
Mr. Miyagi, what are we going to do?

743
00:50:52,500 --> 00:50:55,500
- Where are you going?
- Get fishing pole.

744
00:50:55,600 --> 00:50:56,900
What?

745
00:50:57,700 --> 00:50:59,400
Sometimes I don't get you.

746
00:50:59,500 --> 00:51:03,000
The shop's wrecked. We've just been
robbed, and you're going fishing.

747
00:51:03,100 --> 00:51:05,200
We're flat broke and you're going fishing.

748
00:51:05,200 --> 00:51:08,500
You're just going to fluff it off?
Doesn't this even bother you?

749
00:51:08,500 --> 00:51:13,700
Daniel-<i>san</i>, sometime better be bothered
on full stomach than empty one.

750
00:51:14,100 --> 00:51:17,500
Great, another great thought, huh?
That really does me good.

751
00:51:17,600 --> 00:51:21,300
You go fishing.
I'm going to the police to report it.

752
00:51:21,300 --> 00:51:24,200
Show them the application
so they can arrest these jerks.

753
00:51:24,300 --> 00:51:27,400
This is the '80s,
you gotta do something, Mr. Miyagi.

754
00:51:27,500 --> 00:51:29,800
You can't be so damn passive.

755
00:51:30,400 --> 00:51:33,400
Somebody's gotta do something
about these guys.

756
00:51:49,700 --> 00:51:52,500
I bring the tournament application
to the police station.

757
00:51:52,500 --> 00:51:54,500
As I walk in, they start laughing at me.

758
00:51:54,500 --> 00:51:57,300
Finally the sergeant said,
"Son, we'll look into it."

759
00:51:57,400 --> 00:51:58,900
We'll see. I hope.

760
00:52:00,300 --> 00:52:03,800
I still think you should ask Mr. Miyagi
before going after his tree.

761
00:52:03,900 --> 00:52:06,700
He wouldn't have hidden it
in the middle of nowhere...

762
00:52:06,800 --> 00:52:09,800
...if he wanted people to dig it up.
- I don't have a choice.

763
00:52:09,900 --> 00:52:12,300
If he doesn't sell this tree
we're looking for...

764
00:52:12,400 --> 00:52:14,200
...he loses his business. He's broke.

765
00:52:14,300 --> 00:52:17,400
His social security can barely cover
the expenses on his rowboat.

766
00:52:17,500 --> 00:52:19,800
This tree is like money in the bank.

767
00:52:19,900 --> 00:52:22,100
Great. So now we're robbing a bank.

768
00:52:28,900 --> 00:52:31,300
How much do you think
this thing is worth?

769
00:52:31,400 --> 00:52:36,000
I found out these original <i>bonsai</i> trees
start at $10,000.

770
00:52:36,100 --> 00:52:39,200
- Seriously?
- See, that's why it is so important to me.

771
00:52:39,300 --> 00:52:44,000
This one tree can set Mr. Miyagi up for life.
That's the least I could do for him.

772
00:52:47,000 --> 00:52:48,800
It's a long way down there.

773
00:52:50,300 --> 00:52:52,800
- You know what I think?
- What?

774
00:52:52,900 --> 00:52:58,000
I think when the tide comes in,
the ocean fills up the bottom down there.

775
00:52:58,300 --> 00:53:00,600
Yeah, Mr. Miyagi sure knows
how to pick 'em.

776
00:53:00,700 --> 00:53:02,400
Yeah, no kidding.

777
00:53:03,200 --> 00:53:06,700
How are we supposed to find
Mr. Miyagi's tiny little tree in all this?

778
00:53:06,800 --> 00:53:10,700
He told me he put it halfway down
the steepest cliff...

779
00:53:10,700 --> 00:53:13,300
...where it would catch
the first rays of the sun.

780
00:53:13,400 --> 00:53:15,300
Good luck. We're never gonna find it.

781
00:53:15,400 --> 00:53:18,000
- Wait! That must be it! I found it!
- Are you sure?

782
00:53:18,100 --> 00:53:21,000
God, it's beautiful.
It's like the one on the back of my <i>gi</i>.

783
00:53:21,100 --> 00:53:22,700
Come on, let me see.

784
00:53:22,800 --> 00:53:25,500
You see that ridge, where the sun hits...

785
00:53:25,600 --> 00:53:28,000
It's just like the one on the pot I made.

786
00:53:28,100 --> 00:53:30,300
How are we going to get
all the way down there?

787
00:53:30,400 --> 00:53:34,700
You leave that to me. I'll teach you.
Come on. We gotta go get the ropes.

788
00:53:36,700 --> 00:53:40,300
- You sure you understand everything?
- Yeah, I got it.

789
00:53:40,400 --> 00:53:44,400
I feed this through here
and I hold this back here and I pray to God.

790
00:53:45,500 --> 00:53:50,100
Okay. Now, are you sure
you want to do this?

791
00:53:50,400 --> 00:53:51,700
I wanna do this?

792
00:53:51,900 --> 00:53:55,400
- I gotta do it. I'll be okay.
- You got it. You'll be fine.

793
00:53:55,500 --> 00:53:58,500
Remember, the rope is your friend.
Everything will be great.

794
00:53:58,500 --> 00:54:00,800
Friend? This rope's more than my friend.

795
00:54:00,900 --> 00:54:04,300
I love this rope.
This rope and I are going steady.

796
00:54:04,400 --> 00:54:07,100
Right, rope? Just you and me, rope.

797
00:54:09,100 --> 00:54:12,000
Just lean. Okay, you got it. Don't worry.

798
00:54:12,100 --> 00:54:14,700
Just sit back. Just lean back. You got it.

799
00:54:15,500 --> 00:54:16,800
This is almost fun.

800
00:54:16,800 --> 00:54:19,800
I'm coming, okay? Just keep going.

801
00:54:19,900 --> 00:54:22,300
This isn't so hard.
You're a pretty good teacher.

802
00:54:22,400 --> 00:54:23,600
Thanks.

803
00:54:23,700 --> 00:54:26,300
Daniel! Look out! I got you, okay?

804
00:54:26,400 --> 00:54:30,300
- I'm coming! Daniel, are you okay?
- I'm okay.

805
00:54:30,400 --> 00:54:33,100
Hold on! Don't move, I'm coming.
Stay there.

806
00:54:33,200 --> 00:54:36,700
Okay, I got you. I got you.
Put both hands on the rope.

807
00:54:36,700 --> 00:54:40,800
Put your feet against the rocks
and push out. I got you.

808
00:54:41,300 --> 00:54:45,300
Push out! There you go!
All right, I got you.

809
00:54:45,500 --> 00:54:48,800
Okay, now guide your rope.
Slide your hands to the brake.

810
00:54:48,800 --> 00:54:51,900
To the brake. Right here. All right?

811
00:54:52,800 --> 00:54:56,100
You okay?
Listen, I'm so sorry about the rock.

812
00:54:56,200 --> 00:54:59,300
- You sure you're okay?
- No, I'm fine. Don't worry about it.

813
00:54:59,400 --> 00:55:02,100
God, it's a lot steeper
than it looks from up there, huh?

814
00:55:02,200 --> 00:55:06,900
- You've done this kinda stuff before, right?
- Yeah, but not from this high up.

815
00:55:08,000 --> 00:55:09,100
Great!

816
00:55:09,200 --> 00:55:11,400
Maybe we should go back.
Do you want to?

817
00:55:11,500 --> 00:55:13,700
No, I gotta keep going.
I don't have a choice.

818
00:55:13,800 --> 00:55:17,900
Well, just be careful, okay?
Watch your footing, there you go.

819
00:55:18,300 --> 00:55:20,500
All right. God, you scared me.

820
00:55:20,600 --> 00:55:22,100
I scared you?

821
00:55:22,700 --> 00:55:25,500
- You can get killed doing this.
- Just think positive.

822
00:55:25,500 --> 00:55:28,600
- How are we going to get back up there?
- Don't worry about it.

823
00:55:28,700 --> 00:55:31,300
You're right. I got enough to worry about.

824
00:55:33,700 --> 00:55:36,100
- What?
- Where's the tree?

825
00:55:36,200 --> 00:55:38,700
It's right there, between the two ropes.

826
00:55:39,100 --> 00:55:40,400
Come on.

827
00:55:51,900 --> 00:55:53,700
It's a beautiful tree.

828
00:55:56,900 --> 00:56:00,700
Mr. Miyagi must have looked like
Spider-Man coming down here, huh?

829
00:56:00,700 --> 00:56:02,200
Yeah, no kidding.

830
00:56:02,300 --> 00:56:04,300
Now, remember how I told you to lock off.

831
00:56:04,400 --> 00:56:06,700
Take the rope
and you put it around your butt.

832
00:56:06,800 --> 00:56:09,100
And you tie it around your leg.
Okay, get it?

833
00:56:09,200 --> 00:56:12,200
- There you go. I got it!
- There you go. You got it.

834
00:56:12,300 --> 00:56:15,000
- All right.
- Now you can use both your hands.

835
00:56:16,000 --> 00:56:17,300
All right.

836
00:56:22,300 --> 00:56:24,800
So he really planted this here, huh?

837
00:56:24,900 --> 00:56:28,600
What, this tree? He brought this
all the way back from Okinawa.

838
00:56:30,000 --> 00:56:33,600
What if he tells you to put it back?

839
00:56:34,000 --> 00:56:35,400
What if he does?

840
00:56:35,500 --> 00:56:39,000
He's not going to tell me to put it back.
Believe me, I know this guy.

841
00:56:39,100 --> 00:56:41,000
That <i>bonsai</i> shop
was his dream come true.

842
00:56:41,100 --> 00:56:44,900
- He won't have me put it back.
- I don't think we should be doing this.

843
00:56:45,000 --> 00:56:49,000
I saw his face when he lost his job.
Believe me, I know what I'm doing.

844
00:56:49,000 --> 00:56:51,600
But what about the tree?
Isn't it going to die?

845
00:56:51,700 --> 00:56:55,500
The tree will be fine. The most important
thing is to pack the roots well.

846
00:56:55,700 --> 00:56:58,700
Believe me, he's taught me everything
about these trees.

847
00:56:58,800 --> 00:57:01,800
- Do you want me to take this for you?
- No, I got it.

848
00:57:01,900 --> 00:57:04,400
All I need is a bag to pack the roots in.

849
00:57:04,500 --> 00:57:06,600
- Daniel! Help me up!
- Hang on!

850
00:57:06,600 --> 00:57:09,500
Don't let go! Grab the rope!
Are you okay?

851
00:57:09,600 --> 00:57:10,900
I got it!

852
00:57:11,100 --> 00:57:14,200
Oh, my God! The tree's in the water!
I gotta get it!

853
00:57:16,200 --> 00:57:18,300
It's gonna get washed out!

854
00:57:18,400 --> 00:57:20,100
Move! Hurry up!

855
00:57:20,300 --> 00:57:22,100
Get out of the way!

856
00:57:22,700 --> 00:57:25,100
I gotta get it!
It's gonna get washed out!

857
00:57:25,200 --> 00:57:28,000
The rope! Hurry!
Get the canteen, quick!

858
00:57:28,300 --> 00:57:31,500
We gotta wash the roots off.
The salt water will kill them!

859
00:57:31,500 --> 00:57:34,200
- Is it gonna be okay?
- Mr. Miyagi will know what to do.

860
00:57:34,300 --> 00:57:37,300
- Just move it!
- I got the canteen. It's ready.

861
00:57:37,300 --> 00:57:40,300
We gotta get out of here!
The tide's coming in!

862
00:57:40,400 --> 00:57:42,500
Wash the roots off. Be careful.

863
00:57:42,800 --> 00:57:44,600
All right, let me have it.

864
00:57:44,800 --> 00:57:47,300
- It's soaked.
- You did good. Put it right in there.

865
00:57:47,400 --> 00:57:50,000
Little fella,
I'll have you home in no time.

866
00:57:50,100 --> 00:57:51,700
No big breaks. We're in good shape.

867
00:57:51,800 --> 00:57:54,000
- I just should have tied off better.
- It's not your fault.

868
00:57:54,100 --> 00:57:55,100
Look, it was my idea to...

869
00:57:57,100 --> 00:57:58,300
The ropes.

870
00:58:00,900 --> 00:58:03,700
LaRusso! How you doing?

871
00:58:03,800 --> 00:58:05,300
Heads up, Danny-boy.

872
00:58:05,400 --> 00:58:07,100
Here's something you forgot.

873
00:58:07,200 --> 00:58:09,300
How'd they get here?

874
00:58:10,600 --> 00:58:13,200
- Hey, this isn't a joke anymore.
- I know.

875
00:58:13,400 --> 00:58:14,900
So let the ropes down.

876
00:58:15,000 --> 00:58:15,200
First sign the application.

877
00:58:15,300 --> 00:58:17,200
First sign the application.

878
00:58:17,500 --> 00:58:19,100
Screw you, man!

879
00:58:19,800 --> 00:58:22,200
See, I think you got it backwards,
buddy-boy.

880
00:58:22,300 --> 00:58:24,600
I'm not the one who's screwed here.

881
00:58:24,900 --> 00:58:29,000
Now I figure the tide's gonna come
in about 12 minutes.

882
00:58:30,000 --> 00:58:31,600
Hope you brought a life raft.

883
00:58:31,700 --> 00:58:34,200
How do we get out of here without a rope?

884
00:58:34,600 --> 00:58:38,700
- Without a rope, we're dead.
- We're dead. Yeah, well, this guy's dead.

885
00:58:38,800 --> 00:58:43,100
You're dead. You want me to sign it?
Fine, I'll sign it.

886
00:58:43,200 --> 00:58:45,900
We'll get in the ring
and we'll see who's laughing then.

887
00:58:46,000 --> 00:58:48,400
We'll see who's smiling.
You're gonna be dead meat.

888
00:58:48,500 --> 00:58:49,800
I hate this guy.

889
00:58:50,500 --> 00:58:52,200
Here. I signed it.

890
00:58:52,200 --> 00:58:55,000
You want it? You work for it.
You pull us up!

891
00:58:55,400 --> 00:58:57,600
All right! We'll send them down.

892
00:58:58,900 --> 00:59:00,100
Let them go.

893
00:59:02,600 --> 00:59:04,100
I never learn.

894
00:59:04,300 --> 00:59:07,700
I should have just signed
the damn thing in the first place.

895
00:59:07,800 --> 00:59:10,100
I should have signed it
and gotten it over with.

896
00:59:10,100 --> 00:59:12,000
You didn't know this would happen.

897
00:59:12,100 --> 00:59:14,100
With this guy, I should have known.

898
00:59:14,100 --> 00:59:16,500
I should have known with that guy.

899
00:59:16,600 --> 00:59:19,600
I should have just signed the damn thing.

900
00:59:19,700 --> 00:59:22,300
We wouldn't be stuck down here.
The tree would be safe.

901
00:59:22,400 --> 00:59:26,000
I'm just such a jackass.
Come on, get us out of here!

902
00:59:26,200 --> 00:59:27,800
Come on, pull!

903
00:59:44,400 --> 00:59:46,300
All right, I got you.

904
00:59:51,800 --> 00:59:54,100
You're one heavy wimp, Daniel.

905
00:59:55,600 --> 00:59:57,900
Come on, don't stop. Keep pulling!

906
00:59:58,000 --> 01:00:00,400
- What are you doing?
- Pull us up.

907
01:00:00,500 --> 01:00:02,600
Leave him there. Get the application.

908
01:00:02,700 --> 01:00:05,400
No, you get the application
when I get up there.

909
01:00:07,900 --> 01:00:09,700
- Are you okay?
- Yeah.

910
01:00:09,800 --> 01:00:11,500
All right, here. Just hold us.

911
01:00:11,600 --> 01:00:13,400
- Go get it.
- Here, take it.

912
01:00:15,900 --> 01:00:17,400
Check it out.

913
01:00:18,400 --> 01:00:19,800
It's cool.

914
01:00:20,000 --> 01:00:21,200
That's it.

915
01:00:21,300 --> 01:00:23,900
Don't even think about backing out, man...

916
01:00:24,000 --> 01:00:25,900
...because then I'll really be pissed.

917
01:00:26,000 --> 01:00:28,600
And this, well,
this'll all seem like a happy memory...

918
01:00:28,700 --> 01:00:30,600
...compared to what I'd do to you.

919
01:00:30,700 --> 01:00:32,600
And what we'd all do to her.

920
01:00:32,800 --> 01:00:34,300
Now you're talking.

921
01:00:36,000 --> 01:00:38,400
- Hey!
- Come on! Pull us up!

922
01:00:38,700 --> 01:00:39,900
What, Tarzan?

923
01:00:40,200 --> 01:00:41,400
Pull us up!

924
01:00:41,700 --> 01:00:44,200
- What will you give me?
- I gave you the application.

925
01:00:44,300 --> 01:00:46,200
Yeah, the stakes just went up.

926
01:00:46,200 --> 01:00:48,300
- Give me the tree.
- Daniel, don't!

927
01:00:48,400 --> 01:00:50,200
- No!
- Shut up!

928
01:00:50,700 --> 01:00:52,100
All right.

929
01:00:53,500 --> 01:00:55,500
Just hold us. Don't let go.

930
01:00:58,500 --> 01:01:01,300
Here. Now please be careful with it.

931
01:01:01,500 --> 01:01:03,200
- Please, be careful.
- I will be.

932
01:01:03,300 --> 01:01:06,600
- What are you gonna do with it?
- I'm gonna plant it down there!

933
01:01:06,700 --> 01:01:08,700
- No!
- No, don't, please.

934
01:01:08,800 --> 01:01:11,300
All right, enough. Give me it.

935
01:01:11,400 --> 01:01:13,600
- You want it?
- Just don't throw it over.

936
01:01:13,600 --> 01:01:15,600
Be careful with it, please.

937
01:01:15,600 --> 01:01:16,900
Daniel...

938
01:01:17,800 --> 01:01:19,400
...make a wish.

939
01:01:19,600 --> 01:01:20,700
No!

940
01:01:36,600 --> 01:01:38,000
Mr. Miyagi?

941
01:01:41,400 --> 01:01:42,500
Daniel-<i>san</i>.

942
01:01:43,100 --> 01:01:45,000
The trunk's split. See?

943
01:01:45,500 --> 01:01:50,000
I put the roots in peat moss,
but they got salt water on them...

944
01:01:50,300 --> 01:01:51,400
...and I washed it.

945
01:01:51,500 --> 01:01:54,700
Will you be able to save it?
I didn't mean for this to happen.

946
01:01:54,800 --> 01:01:55,800
I'm sorry.

947
01:01:55,900 --> 01:01:58,200
I just figured maybe we could sell it...

948
01:01:58,300 --> 01:01:59,900
...so we wouldn't have to close.

949
01:01:59,900 --> 01:02:02,900
I didn't want it to be my fault
your dream didn't come true.

950
01:02:02,900 --> 01:02:04,700
Whoever bought it would take good care.

951
01:02:04,800 --> 01:02:06,400
Even better care than yourself.

952
01:02:06,400 --> 01:02:08,800
- Tape. A wide one.
- That's so stupid.

953
01:02:08,900 --> 01:02:11,900
How can someone take care of it
better than where you left it?

954
01:02:12,000 --> 01:02:14,800
- I didn't mean for this to happen.
- Hold.

955
01:02:14,900 --> 01:02:18,800
- I'm sorry. Please forgive me.
- Miyagi forgive you.

956
01:02:18,900 --> 01:02:21,100
You do? I'm such an idiot.

957
01:02:21,600 --> 01:02:24,500
- Is it gonna be okay?
- Depends.

958
01:02:24,700 --> 01:02:27,000
If roots strong, tree survive.

959
01:02:27,300 --> 01:02:29,300
Where do you want these <i>bonsai</i> trees?

960
01:02:29,300 --> 01:02:31,400
Over there on rack, okay. Thank you.

961
01:02:31,500 --> 01:02:33,500
- Trees?
- Peat moss.

962
01:02:33,600 --> 01:02:36,200
Trees? What? What did you do?

963
01:02:36,300 --> 01:02:38,200
Did you buy these?

964
01:02:38,600 --> 01:02:40,000
With what?

965
01:02:40,800 --> 01:02:42,200
Sell truck.

966
01:02:42,700 --> 01:02:44,400
You sold the truck?

967
01:02:47,700 --> 01:02:50,900
Well, why didn't you tell me
that's what you were going to do?

968
01:02:51,000 --> 01:02:53,100
I wake up this morning, you gone.

969
01:02:53,700 --> 01:02:55,000
Damn it!

970
01:02:55,100 --> 01:02:56,900
Why am I so stupid?

971
01:02:58,100 --> 01:03:00,000
No worry, Daniel-<i>san</i>.

972
01:03:00,500 --> 01:03:03,800
Everything work out.
Everything okay now.

973
01:03:03,900 --> 01:03:06,700
Mr. Miyagi,
I signed to fight in the tournament.

974
01:03:14,800 --> 01:03:15,800
Why?

975
01:03:15,900 --> 01:03:18,600
I don't know why.
Because I'm not you, that's why.

976
01:03:18,700 --> 01:03:20,500
I don't always have the right answers.

977
01:03:20,600 --> 01:03:22,800
We were at the bottom.
They pulled the ropes up.

978
01:03:22,900 --> 01:03:24,200
I made a decision on the spot.

979
01:03:24,300 --> 01:03:27,600
It was the wrong one.
What else was I supposed to do?

980
01:03:27,700 --> 01:03:29,100
Understand.

981
01:03:29,500 --> 01:03:30,800
You do?

982
01:03:32,400 --> 01:03:34,700
Listen, Mr. Miyagi,
I gotta be honest with you.

983
01:03:34,700 --> 01:03:37,700
I don't stand a chance against this guy
unless you train me.

984
01:03:37,800 --> 01:03:38,800
Understand.

985
01:03:38,900 --> 01:03:41,400
Well then, you'll train me, right?

986
01:03:42,800 --> 01:03:45,500
Daniel-<i>san</i>, Miyagi always train you.

987
01:03:47,100 --> 01:03:49,400
But for tournament, cannot.

988
01:03:51,700 --> 01:03:53,000
Cannot?

989
01:03:54,000 --> 01:03:56,200
Cannot? What?
What do you mean, cannot?

990
01:03:56,300 --> 01:03:58,700
Mr. Miyagi, why not?

991
01:04:08,400 --> 01:04:10,600
You know what the worst thing was:

992
01:04:10,700 --> 01:04:13,600
When he told me he wouldn't train me
for the tournament.

993
01:04:13,700 --> 01:04:15,800
- Then I knew I was dead.
- What a drag.

994
01:04:15,900 --> 01:04:18,200
Great, let me get some water.
I'm dying of thirst.

995
01:04:18,300 --> 01:04:20,600
- You can't swallow.
- I won't.

996
01:04:20,700 --> 01:04:23,900
You can't keep stopping like this.
You gotta build up your wind.

997
01:04:24,000 --> 01:04:26,100
So bonehead can knock more out of me?

998
01:04:26,200 --> 01:04:28,500
You gotta have more confidence.

999
01:04:28,600 --> 01:04:32,200
- Remember you are the champion.
- Yeah, I'd like to forget it.

1000
01:04:36,100 --> 01:04:37,600
Jessica, this is...

1001
01:04:37,900 --> 01:04:39,100
Hi, there.

1002
01:04:39,200 --> 01:04:41,100
- Sorry, what's your name?
- Terry Silver.

1003
01:04:41,200 --> 01:04:43,300
Terry Silver, this is Jessica Andrews.

1004
01:04:43,400 --> 01:04:46,200
- You training for the Olympics?
- No, it's a tournament.

1005
01:04:46,300 --> 01:04:48,600
The one you won last year?
What's it called?

1006
01:04:48,700 --> 01:04:49,800
The All Valley.

1007
01:04:49,900 --> 01:04:52,800
Right. Good for you.
A champion should defend his title.

1008
01:04:52,900 --> 01:04:55,100
John Kreese told me you had a lot of heart.

1009
01:04:55,200 --> 01:04:57,400
Listen, do you know how to front sweep?

1010
01:04:57,700 --> 01:04:59,000
- Not really.
- Learn.

1011
01:04:59,100 --> 01:05:01,800
Most tournament guys
are suckers for the front sweep.

1012
01:05:01,900 --> 01:05:05,400
You can catch them every time.
Ask your Mr. Miyagi. He'll show you.

1013
01:05:05,500 --> 01:05:08,300
I'm kind of training for this one myself.

1014
01:05:09,000 --> 01:05:10,600
That's too bad.

1015
01:05:10,700 --> 01:05:14,300
I got a good book on sweep techniques.
I'll drop it off for you sometime.

1016
01:05:14,300 --> 01:05:15,500
Great.

1017
01:05:15,600 --> 01:05:18,500
Nice to meet you, Jessica.
Take care of our champion.

1018
01:05:18,600 --> 01:05:20,700
All right, I will. 'Bye.

1019
01:05:22,200 --> 01:05:25,500
That was a nice offer about the book.
Come on, you ready?

1020
01:05:25,600 --> 01:05:27,400
- Let's go. Yes.
- No, I'm pooped.

1021
01:05:27,500 --> 01:05:30,500
- All right, here I come.
- Come on. You're gorgeous. Hurry.

1022
01:05:30,600 --> 01:05:33,300
- Okay, I'm running.
- You gotta get some muscle.

1023
01:05:33,400 --> 01:05:34,900
Oh, man.

1024
01:05:42,200 --> 01:05:44,400
Get out of here! I signed it!

1025
01:05:44,500 --> 01:05:47,100
- Why'd you call the cops?
- Why'd you steal the trees?

1026
01:05:47,200 --> 01:05:48,500
You have no proof.

1027
01:05:48,600 --> 01:05:51,200
Who left the application, the tooth fairy?

1028
01:05:52,000 --> 01:05:53,500
It's your ass, man!

1029
01:05:57,500 --> 01:05:59,700
There's nothing you've got
that I can't counter.

1030
01:05:59,800 --> 01:06:02,700
- Your karate's a joke.
- Let him up, punk!

1031
01:06:03,000 --> 01:06:05,100
- Who are you, his mother?
- Maybe.

1032
01:06:07,900 --> 01:06:09,500
Get up! Get up!

1033
01:06:10,700 --> 01:06:12,900
You see this? You see it?

1034
01:06:15,800 --> 01:06:18,000
Get your hands off me!

1035
01:06:18,100 --> 01:06:20,700
If I see you even on the same street
as this kid...

1036
01:06:20,800 --> 01:06:22,900
...I won't be so charitable with your health.

1037
01:06:23,000 --> 01:06:25,200
- Understand?
- Yes!

1038
01:06:25,700 --> 01:06:28,400
Get the hell out of here.

1039
01:06:28,500 --> 01:06:29,800
Who is that guy?

1040
01:06:29,900 --> 01:06:32,500
- That's the lunatic who wants my title.
- Come on.

1041
01:06:32,600 --> 01:06:36,000
- I was hoping you would kill him.
- That's not what karate's about.

1042
01:06:36,100 --> 01:06:38,000
- It's for defence.
- I know, you're right.

1043
01:06:38,100 --> 01:06:40,600
- Here's your book.
- I brought that for you.

1044
01:06:40,600 --> 01:06:42,200
Right. Thanks.

1045
01:06:42,300 --> 01:06:44,800
There's only so much
you can learn from a book.

1046
01:06:44,800 --> 01:06:46,300
You're telling me.

1047
01:06:46,600 --> 01:06:49,500
Come on, stand up.
Let me show you a couple of moves.

1048
01:06:49,600 --> 01:06:53,300
Help you deal with punks like that.
Make a strong stance.

1049
01:06:53,900 --> 01:06:56,900
Back leg up a little more.
Okay, now sweep me.

1050
01:06:57,000 --> 01:07:01,100
- Well, what do you mean, like that?
- I'm not made of glass. Do it right.

1051
01:07:02,900 --> 01:07:04,000
Better.

1052
01:07:04,100 --> 01:07:07,000
Now a little higher
and at the end twist your hip.

1053
01:07:07,400 --> 01:07:09,200
Keep your hand up.

1054
01:07:12,700 --> 01:07:13,900
Are you okay?

1055
01:07:14,000 --> 01:07:16,500
- I'm sorry. I'm sorry, man.
- That's good.

1056
01:07:16,500 --> 01:07:18,400
That's a strong move.

1057
01:07:19,000 --> 01:07:21,100
Everyone needs a teacher, Daniel.

1058
01:07:21,200 --> 01:07:24,700
I'm opening the Cobra Kai <i>dojo</i> again.
It's time to set things straight.

1059
01:07:24,800 --> 01:07:28,800
Anytime you want to train,
I'll be there for you. No strings attached.

1060
01:07:28,900 --> 01:07:33,700
Thanks. I appreciate that, but...
Listen, thanks for helping me out.

1061
01:07:34,800 --> 01:07:37,300
It's my pleasure.
All right, I'll see you around.

1062
01:07:37,400 --> 01:07:38,800
I'll see you.

1063
01:07:41,900 --> 01:07:43,400
Thanks again.

1064
01:07:56,000 --> 01:07:57,800
- Hi, Jessica.
- Hi, Daniel.

1065
01:07:57,800 --> 01:07:59,300
Hey. Mr. Miyagi.

1066
01:07:59,800 --> 01:08:02,500
Listen, I have a favour to ask of you.

1067
01:08:04,600 --> 01:08:09,400
- Look, Jessica make. Beautiful. You like?
- I stayed up all night firing them.

1068
01:08:09,500 --> 01:08:13,500
I saw one the other night. They're great.
Listen, I have a favour to ask of you.

1069
01:08:13,600 --> 01:08:16,400
I just want to ask you,
do you know how to sweep?

1070
01:08:16,900 --> 01:08:18,200
Of course.

1071
01:08:18,300 --> 01:08:21,200
Would you mind showing me?
I'm not asking you to train me.

1072
01:08:21,300 --> 01:08:23,300
I don't want you to train me. One thing.

1073
01:08:23,400 --> 01:08:26,500
I'd be so appreciative.
All you have to give me is one thing.

1074
01:08:26,600 --> 01:08:30,600
That's it. Please, you gotta do it. Be a pal.

1075
01:08:30,700 --> 01:08:33,100
You wait here. I be right back.

1076
01:08:33,800 --> 01:08:35,200
Where you going?

1077
01:08:35,800 --> 01:08:37,400
Just wait here.

1078
01:08:38,400 --> 01:08:41,600
This is great.
Mr. Miyagi will teach me front sweeps.

1079
01:08:41,700 --> 01:08:45,600
I found out from this guy, tournament guys
are suckers for front sweeps.

1080
01:08:45,700 --> 01:08:48,000
- Really?
- I mean, if I get that down, man, I'm...

1081
01:08:48,100 --> 01:08:52,100
Daniel-<i>san</i>, you hold like this.
First, left sweep...

1082
01:08:52,300 --> 01:08:53,900
It's no joke, all right?

1083
01:08:53,900 --> 01:08:56,600
You don't want to show me,
you don't show me.

1084
01:08:56,700 --> 01:08:59,400
Just don't make fun of me, all right?

1085
01:09:00,800 --> 01:09:04,100
I'm sorry for asking.
Don't worry. It won't happen again.

1086
01:09:53,200 --> 01:09:55,400
- Hey.
- Hi, that was great, man.

1087
01:09:55,500 --> 01:09:57,200
- How you doing?
- Good.

1088
01:09:57,300 --> 01:10:01,200
- Just trying to work the rust out.
- Listen, I gave your offer some thought.

1089
01:10:01,300 --> 01:10:02,300
And?

1090
01:10:02,400 --> 01:10:05,300
If it's not too much trouble,
I'd like to take you up on it.

1091
01:10:05,400 --> 01:10:07,800
I mean,
you know, just on a short-term basis.

1092
01:10:07,900 --> 01:10:10,800
Trouble, are you kidding?
lt'd be an honour.

1093
01:10:10,900 --> 01:10:13,400
How does Mr. Miyagi feel about it?

1094
01:10:14,900 --> 01:10:16,700
Well, Mr. Miyagi...

1095
01:10:19,000 --> 01:10:21,800
...doesn't need to know about it, if...

1096
01:10:22,900 --> 01:10:25,700
- But he knows you're competing?
- He knows that.

1097
01:10:25,700 --> 01:10:27,600
He just doesn't approve.

1098
01:10:29,900 --> 01:10:32,300
Everybody has a right to his opinion.

1099
01:10:32,400 --> 01:10:35,300
- Look, I won't say anything.
- Thanks.

1100
01:10:35,400 --> 01:10:37,500
So, when do you want to start?

1101
01:10:37,500 --> 01:10:40,500
No, I mean, that's up to you.
Whenever it's...

1102
01:10:40,600 --> 01:10:43,300
I got a <i>gi</i> hanging in the closet.
I think it'll fit.

1103
01:10:43,400 --> 01:10:45,600
What do you say we go right now?

1104
01:10:45,700 --> 01:10:46,800
Now?

1105
01:10:47,500 --> 01:10:48,600
One more.

1106
01:10:50,700 --> 01:10:53,500
Good. Catch your breath.
Come on over here.

1107
01:10:53,600 --> 01:10:55,900
You're better than I thought.

1108
01:10:56,100 --> 01:10:58,800
You're ready to move on, Mr. LaRusso.

1109
01:10:58,900 --> 01:11:00,600
You're ready to move on.

1110
01:11:00,700 --> 01:11:03,300
There are three things
that make a champion.

1111
01:11:03,400 --> 01:11:07,800
The three "D"s:
Desire, devotion and discipline.

1112
01:11:08,000 --> 01:11:09,700
The first two I can't give you.

1113
01:11:09,800 --> 01:11:12,900
The last one I can,
but you have to be willing to receive it.

1114
01:11:12,900 --> 01:11:14,800
Are you, Mr. LaRusso?

1115
01:11:15,400 --> 01:11:16,700
Sure.

1116
01:11:17,800 --> 01:11:20,300
The response you're looking for is,
"Yes, sir."

1117
01:11:20,400 --> 01:11:23,800
- Right. Yes, sir. I'm sorry.
- That's okay. Stand up straight.

1118
01:11:23,800 --> 01:11:28,400
Now, over the years I've developed
a system of intensive short-term training...

1119
01:11:28,500 --> 01:11:30,500
...for situations just like this.

1120
01:11:30,600 --> 01:11:32,800
It comes in two parts and has three rules.

1121
01:11:32,900 --> 01:11:35,700
- I call it "Quick Silver."
- That's good.

1122
01:11:37,000 --> 01:11:38,600
You like that, huh?

1123
01:11:39,300 --> 01:11:40,900
Rule Number One:

1124
01:11:41,000 --> 01:11:43,500
A man can't stand, he can't fight.

1125
01:11:44,500 --> 01:11:45,900
Repeat it.

1126
01:11:46,400 --> 01:11:48,200
A man can't stand, he can't fight.

1127
01:11:48,200 --> 01:11:50,400
With conviction, Mr. LaRusso.

1128
01:11:50,700 --> 01:11:54,500
- A man can't stand, he can't fight.
- Good. All right.

1129
01:11:55,300 --> 01:11:59,300
Imagine these two-by-fours are legs.
Sweep them.

1130
01:12:01,500 --> 01:12:03,200
What are you...

1131
01:12:14,300 --> 01:12:15,900
That's too low.

1132
01:12:16,800 --> 01:12:20,100
Any higher it'd be like hitting the knee.
Right?

1133
01:12:20,400 --> 01:12:23,400
Did you come here
to teach or to be taught?

1134
01:12:32,200 --> 01:12:34,800
We're not sweeping floors here. Harder.

1135
01:12:35,500 --> 01:12:38,800
Come on, put your hip into it.
That's where the power is.

1136
01:12:40,200 --> 01:12:41,900
That's it. Harder.

1137
01:12:43,500 --> 01:12:44,700
Harder.

1138
01:12:50,200 --> 01:12:53,300
"Ow" is not an acceptable <i>kiai</i> in this <i>dojo</i>,
Mr. LaRusso.

1139
01:12:53,400 --> 01:12:57,100
Isn't this a little bit extreme, sir?
I mean, come on.

1140
01:12:58,000 --> 01:13:01,300
Extreme situations
require extreme measures.

1141
01:13:18,900 --> 01:13:21,600
Now, you come back tomorrow.
We'll start again.

1142
01:13:25,600 --> 01:13:27,800
You did good for your first day.

1143
01:13:30,100 --> 01:13:31,400
Thanks.

1144
01:13:38,800 --> 01:13:40,800
I really appreciate all your help.

1145
01:13:40,800 --> 01:13:43,000
- Thanks again.
- You're welcome.

1146
01:14:20,300 --> 01:14:22,000
Who is it?

1147
01:14:26,400 --> 01:14:28,400
Why don't you come in?

1148
01:14:30,700 --> 01:14:33,200
Just catching up on some sit-ups here.

1149
01:14:33,400 --> 01:14:36,500
You know, it's not easy
when you're training yourself.

1150
01:14:36,700 --> 01:14:39,200
What happened foot?

1151
01:14:41,200 --> 01:14:42,600
What foot?

1152
01:14:46,100 --> 01:14:47,900
Look at that!

1153
01:14:48,700 --> 01:14:50,200
I don't know.

1154
01:14:50,800 --> 01:14:53,700
Maybe I banged it in my sleep.
I don't remember.

1155
01:14:54,800 --> 01:14:57,600
- What's that?
- You soak foot.

1156
01:14:57,800 --> 01:14:59,600
Be better tomorrow.

1157
01:14:59,600 --> 01:15:04,800
- You got a new foot in there for me?
- No. Next best thing. New foot powder.

1158
01:15:08,900 --> 01:15:11,600
Smells like old foot powder.
What's in there?

1159
01:15:11,800 --> 01:15:15,400
Better you don't know. Give me foot.

1160
01:15:21,100 --> 01:15:23,400
- It's hot!
- Hot, hot...

1161
01:15:24,700 --> 01:15:26,000
Good.

1162
01:15:28,500 --> 01:15:32,000
Maybe tomorrow
you remember what happened foot?

1163
01:15:32,100 --> 01:15:33,700
Then you tell Miyagi.

1164
01:15:33,800 --> 01:15:36,200
Tomorrow? No.

1165
01:15:36,300 --> 01:15:40,300
I have so many things to do tomorrow.
Tomorrow, I'm busy.

1166
01:15:42,100 --> 01:15:46,400
Tomorrow is a bad day.
In the morning, I'm supposed to...

1167
01:15:46,500 --> 01:15:50,300
In the afternoon, I'm meeting with
a buddy of mine I haven't seen since...

1168
01:15:50,400 --> 01:15:53,500
...we got back, you know, from Okinawa.

1169
01:15:58,900 --> 01:16:00,600
What am I doing?

1170
01:16:03,400 --> 01:16:05,100
What am I doing?

1171
01:16:36,600 --> 01:16:39,200
Hope confusion end soon.

1172
01:16:42,400 --> 01:16:45,200
Miyagi heart empty without you.

1173
01:16:50,000 --> 01:16:55,200
The bruise on your foot is gone.
That's good. You're a fast healer.

1174
01:16:56,300 --> 01:16:58,000
All right, let's go.

1175
01:16:58,700 --> 01:17:01,500
That's a nice move.
Mr. Miyagi teach you that?

1176
01:17:01,700 --> 01:17:04,000
- No.
- I didn't think so.

1177
01:17:04,100 --> 01:17:07,400
- What was the last thing he taught you?
- We did <i>kata</i>.

1178
01:17:07,500 --> 01:17:09,300
- <i>Kata</i>?
- Yeah.

1179
01:17:09,400 --> 01:17:12,900
<i>Kata</i> is good for working up a sweat.
It won't win the tournament.

1180
01:17:12,900 --> 01:17:15,100
Come on over here. Hold the bag.

1181
01:17:15,200 --> 01:17:18,200
Rule Number Two
of the "Quick Silver" method:

1182
01:17:18,400 --> 01:17:20,900
A man can't breathe, he can't fight.

1183
01:17:21,300 --> 01:17:23,500
Now, imagine this is the enemy.

1184
01:17:23,600 --> 01:17:26,500
These are his ribs, behind them his lungs.

1185
01:17:30,500 --> 01:17:32,400
- You got it?
- Yeah.

1186
01:17:32,500 --> 01:17:34,200
Good. You try it.

1187
01:17:37,200 --> 01:17:39,600
Wait a minute. Let's do it over here.

1188
01:17:39,700 --> 01:17:42,000
- Where?
- Right here, his ribs.

1189
01:17:42,100 --> 01:17:43,600
Lay into him.

1190
01:17:50,600 --> 01:17:53,200
Why do I have to do this with this thing?

1191
01:17:54,400 --> 01:17:56,700
Because it's part of the training.

1192
01:17:56,900 --> 01:17:59,600
Because I'm teaching you
techniques you don't have.

1193
01:17:59,700 --> 01:18:02,100
Techniques you need
to win the tournament.

1194
01:18:02,200 --> 01:18:05,200
What, do you think you can rely
on that crane crap?

1195
01:18:05,400 --> 01:18:07,700
I did pretty well with it last time.

1196
01:18:09,900 --> 01:18:12,600
Wake up and smell the coffee.

1197
01:18:13,100 --> 01:18:15,500
Last time you weren't fighting this.

1198
01:18:18,900 --> 01:18:21,000
You don't get it, do you?

1199
01:18:22,800 --> 01:18:27,000
If you want to lose because of a little pain,
I can't be a part of that.

1200
01:18:27,100 --> 01:18:29,900
I make wimps into winners,
not the other way around.

1201
01:18:30,000 --> 01:18:32,100
Christ, I'm wasting my time.

1202
01:20:05,400 --> 01:20:06,500
Yeah?

1203
01:20:09,800 --> 01:20:12,600
Damn it! Can you come back later?

1204
01:20:12,700 --> 01:20:15,000
Why are you doing this to yourself?

1205
01:20:15,100 --> 01:20:16,300
Doing what?

1206
01:20:16,600 --> 01:20:18,300
What you doing.

1207
01:20:19,200 --> 01:20:20,500
Because...

1208
01:20:22,100 --> 01:20:25,800
...extreme situations
require extreme measures, okay?

1209
01:20:27,600 --> 01:20:30,000
That not sound like you talking.

1210
01:20:31,700 --> 01:20:33,700
It is me talking, all right?

1211
01:20:33,800 --> 01:20:36,900
I'm sorry if you don't like it,
but I got problems...

